<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Best Svix Alternatives (2026) — Open-Source Webhook Platforms Compared</title>
    <%
    locals.pageTitle = 'Best Svix Alternatives (2026) — Open-Source Webhook Platforms Compared';
    locals.pageDescription = 'Evaluating Svix? Compare Hook0, Hookdeck, Convoy & more. Side-by-side on pricing, self-hosting, licensing, and what "open-source" means in practice.';
    locals.pageCanonical = '/svix-alternatives';
    locals.pageFAQSchema = {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Svix truly open-source?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Partially. Svix's base is MIT-licensed, but enterprise features (SSO, advanced analytics, priority support) are proprietary and closed-source. This is called open-core. You can run the community edition, but key production features require a paid plan. Hook0, by contrast, ships everything under SSPL-1.0 with no closed-source add-ons."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can I self-host Svix for free?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "You can self-host the MIT-licensed community edition, but enterprise features are not included. Full self-hosting with all features requires Svix's enterprise plan. Hook0 and Convoy both offer free self-hosting with full feature parity."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best Svix alternative for startups?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Hook0 works well for startups. Free tier, no credit card, per-event pricing starting at €59/month, and free self-hosting via Docker or Kubernetes. The company is 100% bootstrapped, so there is no VC pushing to raise prices next quarter. Convoy is worth a look too if MPL-2.0 licensing matters to you."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How does Svix pricing compare to alternatives?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Svix offers a free tier and per-event paid plans, but self-hosting and enterprise features require enterprise pricing (contact sales). Hook0 Cloud starts at €59/month with transparent pricing and includes self-hosting for free on any plan. Hookdeck is cloud-only with per-event pricing. Convoy is self-hosted only with enterprise pricing for support. HostedHooks offers cloud-only paid plans."
          }
        }
      ]
    };
    %>
    <%- include('./includes/_head.ejs') %>
</head>
<body>
<%- include('./includes/_header.ejs') %>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="relative gradient-hero overflow-hidden py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-50"></div>
    <div class="blur-circle blur-circle--indigo w-96 h-96 -top-48 -left-48"></div>
    <div class="blur-circle blur-circle--green w-80 h-80 top-1/2 -right-40"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <span class="section__eyebrow">Comparison</span>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-display-xl text-white">
            Looking for a Svix Alternative?
            <span class="block text-gradient-green">Open-Source Webhook Platforms Compared</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-body-lg text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Svix is a good webhook platform. It is not the only one. If you care about full open-source licensing, free self-hosting, EU data residency, or a vendor that won't jack up prices after a Series B, this page breaks down your options.
        </p>

        <!-- CTA Buttons -->
        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="https://app.hook0.com/register" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg group" onclick="trackEvent('CTA', 'Click', 'svix-alternatives-hero-register')">
                Start Free with Hook0
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
                </svg>
            </a>
            <a href="https://play.hook0.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" onclick="trackEvent('CTA', 'Click', 'svix-alternatives-hero-playground')">
                Try the Playground
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<%- include('./includes/_social-proof-bar.ejs') %>

<!-- Why Consider Alternatives -->
<section class="section relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-20"></div>
    <div class="blur-circle blur-circle--green w-64 h-64 top-1/4 right-0 opacity-10"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-12 animate-on-scroll">
            <span class="section__eyebrow">Why Look Beyond Svix</span>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-display font-bold text-white">Why Teams Look Elsewhere</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 stagger-children">
            <!-- Open-Core Limitations -->
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-8">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4"></path>
                    </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Open-Core Limitations</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">
                    Svix's MIT base is real open-source. The catch: enterprise features like SSO, advanced analytics, and dedicated support are proprietary. When you scale, you hit a paywall. If your team needs full source access, that's a problem.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- VC Pressure -->
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-8">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-indigo-500/10 border border-indigo-500/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-indigo-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                    </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">$17M in VC Means Pressure</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">
                    Venture capital expects a return. Svix raised $17M -- that money has to come back somehow, usually through price hikes, feature gating, or an acquisition. A bootstrapped vendor doesn't have that pressure.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- No EU Hosting -->
            <div class="animate-on-scroll card card--glow p-8">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/20 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
                    <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
                    </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">No European Hosting</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400">
                    Svix is US-based and has no EU cloud option. If you're subject to GDPR or data sovereignty rules, that's a blocker. You could self-host, but that requires their enterprise plan.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Comparison Table -->
